io.scanbot.sdk.ui.view.workflow.camera

Class WorkflowFrameHandler

  • io.scanbot.sdk.ui.view.workflow.camera.WorkflowFrameHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FrameHandler

    public class WorkflowFrameHandler
implements FrameHandler

    Performs contour detection on camera preview frames. Outputs results via interface WorkflowFrameHandler.ResultHandler (.addResultHandler).

    Preview frame considered intercepted if at least one interface WorkflowFrameHandler.ResultHandler returns true from WorkflowFrameHandler.ResultHandler.handleFrameResult

    See Also:
    interface WorkflowFrameHandler.ResultHandler, .addResultHandler, interface WorkflowFrameHandler.ResultHandler, WorkflowFrameHandler.ResultHandler.handleFrameResult, interface PreviewBuffer

      • handleFrame

        @Synchronized
public boolean handleFrame(@NotNull
                                         io.scanbot.sdk.camera.FrameHandler.Frame previewFrame)

        Invoked for every new camera preview frame

        Parameters:
        previewFrame - captured preview frame data
        Returns:
        true if frame should be considered as "intercepted", i.e. no further processing should be performed on it. false to allow other frame handlers to process this frame.

      • addResultHandler

        public void addResultHandler(@NotNull
                             io.scanbot.sdk.ui.view.workflow.camera.WorkflowFrameHandler.ResultHandler handler)

        Registers result handler which will be notified about workflow results.

        Results are coming on the worker thread. Don't forget to move execution to main thread before updating UI.

        Parameters:
        handler - handler to register. Must not be null. If handler was alreadyregistered, nothing happens.
